<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 5:23PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Portage, southern
Trumbull, Mahoning, Stark, southern Summit, Wayne and eastern Holmes
Counties through 630 PM EDT...
At 522 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Ravenna to near Green to near Wooster.
Movement was southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail. The strong gusts
may occur well-ahead of the storms.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Akron, Canton, Youngstown, Warren, Wooster, Salem, Ravenna,
Columbiana, Boardman, Massillon, Kent, Barberton, Green, Alliance,
Niles, Tallmadge, North Canton, Streetsboro, Louisville and Orrville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
